24:["$","div","principal",{"className":"row align-items-start mb-100 ","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"col-lg-4","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"leader-image-wrap mb-40 text-center","children":[["$","div",null,{"style":{"backgroundColor":"#f5f5f5","borderRadius":"10px","height":"400px","display":"flex","alignItems":"center","justifyContent":"center","overflow":"hidden"},"children":["$","p",null,{"children":["[REPLACE_WITH_PHOTO: ","Mrs. S. Nalini","]"]}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"leader-info mt-20","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"mb-0","style":{"color":"#1A3C6E"},"children":"Mrs. S. Nalini"}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"color":"#F5A623","fontWeight":"bold"},"children":"Principal, Sree Jayam School"}]]}]]}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"col-lg-8","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"leader-message-wrap pl-30 pr-30","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"mb-30","style":{"borderLeft":"4px solid #F5A623","paddingLeft":"20px"},"children":"Message"}],["$","div",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"1.05rem","lineHeight":"1.7","whiteSpace":"pre-line"},"children":"Dear Students and Parents,\n\nGreetings from Sree Jayam School.\n\nEducation is not merely the pursuit of academic excellence, but the journey of shaping character, values, and a sense of responsibility towards society.\n\nAt SJS, we believe that every child is unique and holds immense potential. Our aim is to nurture young minds with knowledge, discipline, and compassion, enabling them to grow into confident and responsible individuals. Along with academics, we encourage students to develop critical thinking, creativity, and strong moral values.\n\nWith the support of our dedicated teachers and the cooperation of parents, we guide our students to achieve their best and become responsible individuals.\n\nLet us continue to work together to create an environment where learning is joyful, meaningful and inspiring.\n\nI wish all our students a successful and bright future."}]]}]}]]}]
33:T67e,Dear Students, Parents, and Educators,

As we commence the 2026-27 academic session at Sree Jayam School, we reaffirm our commitment to the rigorous standards of the Council for the Indian School Certificate Examinations (CISCE). Our pedagogical mission this year centers on a fundamental shift: moving from passive instruction toward active, student-led discovery.

Central to our approach is the cultivation of disciplined self-study habits. True intellectual maturity is achieved when a student transitions from being a consumer of information to an architect of their own knowledge. By mastering the art of independent inquiry, our students develop the resilience and analytical depth required by the ICSE curriculum and the global landscape beyond it.

Furthermore, we uphold the Right to Learn as an open, practical, and collaborative process. In our classrooms, the teacher's role is that of a skilled facilitator — bridging the gap between theoretical concepts and real-world application. We encourage an environment where students engage deeply with their educators through dialogue, laboratory experimentation, and project-based inquiry. This ensures that learning is not a monologue of facts, but a practical exploration of truths.

This journey is a triad of commitment: students must take ownership of their preparation, parents must provide a disciplined environment for reflection, and faculty must provide the mentorship that sparks curiosity. Let us work in unison to ensure that every student at Sree Jayam School achieves their fullest potential, emerging as a self-reliant, articulate, and principled leader of tomorrow.

With warm regards.25:["$","div","academic-director",{"className":"row align-items-start mb-100 flex-row-reverse","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"col-lg-4","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"leader-image-wrap mb-40 text-center","children":[["$","div",null,{"style":{"backgroundColor":"#f5f5f5","borderRadius":"10px","height":"400px","display":"flex","alignItems":"center","justifyContent":"center","overflow":"hidden"},"children":["$","p",null,{"children":["[REPLACE_WITH_PHOTO: ","Mr. Kiran Baskar S","]"]}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"leader-info mt-20","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"mb-0","style":{"color":"#1A3C6E"},"children":"Mr. Kiran Baskar S"}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"color":"#F5A623","fontWeight":"bold"},"children":"Academic Director, Sree Jayam School"}]]}]]}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"col-lg-8","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"leader-message-wrap pl-30 pr-30","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"mb-30","style":{"borderLeft":"4px solid #F5A623","paddingLeft":"20px"},"children":"Message"}],["$","div",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"1.05rem","lineHeight":"1.7","whiteSpace":"pre-line"},"children":"$33"}]]}]}]]}]
